  В«TD1В»В«BO Inner ProductВ»В«В»Z[i;j] is f / A[i] g B[j]. Row A[;j] is multiplied
                           with column B[i;] and the resulting vector V is
                           then f-reduced to give the scalar Z[i;j] (enclosed
                           if necessary to yield a scalar).
                       В«В»  For simple numeric matrices A and B this is
                           the "matrix multiplication" known from linear
                           algebra.
  В«TD2В»В«APL вҠўAвҶҗ2 2вҚҙ1 2 3 4В»В«APL вҠўBвҶҗ2 2вҚҙ1 2 3 4В»В«APL вҠўA +.Г— BВ»
